# Pause or Activate an Ad

Pausing or activating an ad from the Ads submenu will determine the status of the ad across all associated placements.

To pause an ad on an individual placement, take action from the placement Ad Inspector via quick actions.

## Pause or Activate an individual Ad across all Placements

1. In the main menu, click **[!UICONTROL Campaigns]**.
1. Click the name of the campaign.
1. In the submenu, click **[!UICONTROL Ads]**.
1. Next to the ad name, click  **[!UICONTROL ...]** > **[!UICONTROL Pause]** or **[!UICONTROL Activate]**.

## Pause or Activate multiple Ads across all Placements

1. In the main menu, click **[!UICONTROL Campaigns]**.
1. Click the name of the campaign.
1. In the submenu, click **[!UICONTROL Ads]**.
1. Click the **[!UICONTROL Check Box]** next to the ad name.
1. Select **[!UICONTROL Edit]** in the bulk operations pop up bar.
1. Choose your edit mode.
1. Select **[!UICONTROL Submit]**

## Pause or Activate an Ad on an Individual Placement

1. In the main menu, click **[!UICONTROL Campaigns]**.
1. Click the name of the campaign.
1. In the submenu, click **[!UICONTROL Placements]**.
1. Next to the placement name, click  **[!UICONTROL ...]** > **[!UICONTROL Ads]**.
1. Next to the ad name, click  **[!UICONTROL ...]** > **[!UICONTROL Pause]** or **[!UICONTROL Activate]**.

>[!NOTE]
>
>If an Ad has been paused from the Ads submenu it cannot be activated from the Placement Inspector. **[!UICONTROL Activate]** from the Ads submenu first.  

